---
description: Cloudflare Worker API, auth, quotas, and server-side AI boundaries
globs: ["worker/**/*", "src/data/api.ts", "src/data/apiConfig.ts", "src/lib/ai/basicProvider.ts", "server.mjs"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Reference: `worker/README.md`, `worker/src/index.ts`, `scripts/verify-worker.mjs`.

- Validate Supabase bearer token at every protected route; never trust client-supplied user IDs.
- Service-role key stays server-side only (`worker/.dev.vars`, Wrangler secrets).
- Enforce scoped CORS via `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`; reject unknown origins in production.
- Bound input/output (Zod schemas); enforce quota through existing Supabase RPCs.
- Support idempotent retries for turn and evaluation actions where implemented.
- Return safe error categories; do not leak secrets, stack traces, or internal paths.
- Handle provider failures honestly; no fabricated AI responses.
- Local dev: `npm run api:worker:dev`; tests: `npm run api:worker:test`; deploy verify: `npm run api:worker:verify`.
